Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Dual street frontage to Hay & Cook St

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
1298 Hay Street, West Perth presents an exceptional two storey character building on a 461sqm* land parcel convenient to the core retail and business hub of West Perth available for sale and lease.

Located on the northern side of Hay Street the property benefits from excellent street level exposure with the convenience of rear access via Cook Street providing 7 rear cay bays including a secure garage for a single vehicle.

The building is currently configured providing 13 main rooms with 6 main rooms downstairs plus two small storage rooms, a tea room plus male and female bathroom amenities. Upstairs features 7 main rooms plus two small storage rooms, a tea room and two balcony areas.

Currently, 3 downstairs rooms are leased to Ian Lowther Physiotherapy occupying 3 downstairs rooms paying a net rental of $21,417.96 per annum.

The building provides tremendous flexibility to be occupied by single or multiple tenants.

We note there is no heritage listing on the building and the property is zoned ‘Town Centre’ offering future development potential.

This genuine opportunity is suitable for investors, owner occupiers and future developers.

The property is offered for sale via Private Treaty.

*Approx

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: FREESTANDING WEST PERTH CHARACTER OFFICE - AVAILABLE FOR SALE AND LEASE

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Located on the ground floor on vibrant Colin Street West Perth on the fringe of the Perth CBD, this recently refurbished office/medical suite is at the entrance of the complex and offers convenient access for the occupier and/or their clients.

Boasting excellent natural light, convenient public transport access, great interaction with the street and a generous 4 exclusive tandem car bays this is a chance to secure quality, centrally located accommodation at affordable rates.

A unique, small tenancy in a high profile, easy access position.

Rick McKenzie - 0405 361 879

On behalf of Centuria, CBRE and JLL are pleased to present the opportunity to acquire a 100% freehold interest in a premium healthcare asset, Perth Clinic, located at 21-29 Havelock Street, West Perth WA. 

Comprising some 4,856 sqm of accommodation, the three-level mental health hospital is complimented by an adjacent, recently refurbished office building occupied by specialist doctors and Perth Clinic administration.

The property is wholly leased to Perth Clinic until January 2033 and is Perth’s largest mental healthcare facility, which has operated from the property since 1996.  

The purpose-built hospital and consists of 100 licenced beds with private ensuites, a specialised treatment theatre, commercial-scale kitchen and various administrative and group session rooms. 

Strategically located on Havelock Street in West Perth, opposite Parliament House and only 900m from the Perth CBD, the property occupies a 4,487 sqm corner site making it one of the largest land holdings in the tightly held West Perth market.

The Perth Clinic represents an exceptionally rare opportunity to acquire a long WALE asset in the highly coveted healthcare sector and is the most significant healthcare asset to be offered to market in Perth in recent times.

The property is offered for sale via an Expressions of Interest campaign closing Friday 18th June 2021 at 2pm AWST.

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Adjacent to City West Train Station

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
This is an outstanding opportunity for an owner occupier or investor to secure 318sqm* of contemporary ground floor offices in a modern, high quality building. 

The current lay out is largely open plan, including a spacious kitchen/breakout area, as well as a boardroom and 2 x perimeter offices/meeting rooms. The unit is fully air-conditioned and self-contained, with direct access available from the basement car park that provides 8 secure parking bays.

Situated on the Northern end of Colin street opposite the picturesque Totterdell Park, 162 Colin Street is located within walking distance to City West Train Station and easily accessible from both freeways and major arterial roads.

The property benefits from its proximity to the thriving West Perth café and retail strip, as well as the Watertown & City West retail precincts. 

Property Highlights include
-	318sqm* of contemporary offices
-	8 secure basement car parking bays
-	Mix of open plan and partitioned layout 
-	Fully self-contained facilities including disabled toilets
-	Air conditioned
-	Abundant natural light
